:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Okt 22, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent wide\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104lfa1665703523288.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/lfa1665703523288.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/lfa1665703523288.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"lfa1665703523288\" role=\"article\">\n<div class=\"body conbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Refer to information regarding the tools, resources, and conventions for\n    Uniface.</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\" id=\"lfa1665703523288__ul_pmf_zgf_zwb\">\n<li class=\"li\"><a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"pqr1665702919772.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/pqr1665702919772.html\" title=\"Uniface provides many tools and servers for developing, integrating, deploying, and running complex, component-based applications. Some tools are available in the Uniface IDE, others are standalone utilities. Many utilities are available from the command line, enabling them to be used in batch mode.\">Uniface Tools</a></li>\n<li class=\"li\"><a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"hxc1665702744973.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/hxc1665702744973.html\" title=\"Uniface provides a command line interface that enables you to access many functions without actually opening the user interface. By running a Uniface executable (such as ide.exe or uniface) with command line switches you can compile objects, debug applications, import and export, specify assignment files, and more.\">Uniface Command Line Interface</a></li>\n<li class=\"li\"><a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"nry1665702619485.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/nry1665702619485.html\" title=\"Uniface provides a default set of templates and snippets that enable you to create new development objects and components that can work immediately. In fact, it is not possible to create a new object without a template.\">Uniface Default Templates</a></li>\n<li class=\"li\"><a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"sjo1665702919851.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/sjo1665702919851.html\" title=\"During installation, a large number of files and executables are installed. Some of the most important are described in the topics in this section.\">Uniface Files and Executables</a></li>\n<li class=\"li\"><a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"yoi1665702919920.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/yoi1665702919920.html\" title=\"Uniface delivers a set of glyphs for use in its own tools and editors. New glyphs are added in each new version of Uniface, sometimes replacing older glyphs, sometimes as additions.\">Uniface Glyphs</a></li>\n<li class=\"li\"><a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"gbf1665703541848.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/gbf1665703541848.html\" title=\"The Uniface IDE uses icons to represent development objects and indicate whether they inherit from another object.\">Uniface Icons</a></li>\n<li class=\"li\"><a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"cwu1665702919990.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/cwu1665702919990.html\" title=\"The maximum values that occur throughout Uniface are inherent limits that you need to consider as you develop applications. Your DBMS or operating system may impose further restrictions of its own.\">Uniface Maximums</a></li>\n<li class=\"li\"><a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"xyj1722408509428.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/xyj1722408509428.html\" title=\"The name of a development object is its unique identifier. When naming development objects, use the allowed syntax for the object name. Avoid using words that are reserved for use within Uniface and your own environment, including the operating system and database.\">Naming Rules for Uniface Development Objects</a></li>\n<li class=\"li\"><a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"ujc1665702619229.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ujc1665702619229.html\" title=\"Reserved words are terms that cannot be used to name your Rocket Uniface objects.\">Uniface Reserved Words</a></li>\n<li class=\"li\"><a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"zcc1665702920067.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/zcc1665702920067.html\" title=\"A retrieve profile is used to control the scope of the data to be retrieved from the database. It consists of one or more values for one or more fields in an entity, often containing profile characters. In essence, a retrieve profile is a search query.\">Retrieve Profile Characters</a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2529537\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2529537\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Tools, Resources, and Conventions Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Okt 22, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Refer to information regarding the tools, resources, and conventions for Uniface. Uniface Tools Uniface Command Line Interface Uniface Default Templates Uniface Files and Executables Uniface Glyphs Uniface Icons Uniface Maximums Naming Rules for Uniface Development Objects Uniface Reserved Words Retrieve Profile Characters Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}